	Original slave by Mr.Larmer/Wanted Team in 1998.

	Version 1.3 (09.01.2002) by Wepl:

	- Support for HitSquad version added
	- New imager, uses files now
	- All files can compressed using FImp/ProPack
	- Snoop bugs fixed

	Version 1.4 (04.04.2008) by Wepl:

	- Removed a strange check which caused one version to
	  fail on uae, thanks to Toni Wilen for research
	- New install script
	- Icons and hints added
	- Source included

	Version 1.5 (20.10.09) by Hungry Horace:

	- High Score table load/save (to file: MidnightResistance.highs)
	- Optional Patch to double the palette colours, correcting the
		error made in the game's conversion
	- Second-fire buttons can now be used to activate second weapon
	- CD32 Controls Added
		- Blue for Second Weapon
		- Green for extra Jump button
		- Yellow to toggle sound-fx/music
		- Play to pause the game
	- Fixed bug preventing player 2 from using second weapon 
	  	whilst moving.

	- Additional Options on CUSTOM1
		1 = Double-Brightness Palette
		2 = CD32 Control Mode (both ports)
		4 = Switch Green/Blue CD32 buttons, or use 
			second fire button to jump.
	   - Add values together for combinations of the above 
		(e.g. CUSTOM1=3 to enable Brightness and CD32 Controls)
		
	- Trainers on CUSTOM2
		1 = Infinite Lives
		2 = Infinite Credits
		4 = Infinite Ammo (both weapons)
		8 = Infinite Money
	   - Add values together for combinatations of the above 
		(e.g. CUSTOM2=6 to enable infinite Credits and Ammo)
			
	- Trainers on CUSTOM3
		0 = Nothing	/  1 = Supercharge on
		2 = Barrier on	/  3 = Supercharge & Barrier on

	- Trainer on CUSTOM4 sets Weapon 1
		0 = None 	/  1 = Shotgun
		2 = Blue thing	/  3 = Auto
		4 = Fire	/  5 = Three-Way

	- Trainer on CUSTOM5 sets Weapon 2
		0 = None	/  1 = Homing Missiles
		2 = Nitro	/  3 = Shower
	
	- High Score saving is disabled if any of CUSTOM2/3/4/5 are used

	Version 1.6 (10.07.13) by Hungry Horace:

	- Fixed bug on CUSTOM4 Trainer
	- Improved second button support
	- Configuration Features for WHDLoad v17+ added
